00007 ORDictionary::ORDictionary(const ORDictionary& dict) : ORVDictValue(dict)
00008 {
00009   SetName(dict.fName);
00010   /* Now the hard part, copying the dictionary map correctly calling 
00011      all the copy constructors. */ 
00012   std::map<const std::string, ORVDictValue*>::const_iterator dictIter;
00013   for (dictIter = dict.fDictMap.begin();dictIter!=dict.fDictMap.end();dictIter++) {
00014     EValType type = dictIter->second->GetValueType(); 
00015     ORVDictValue* insertDictValue = NULL;
00016     switch (type) {
00017       case kDict:
00018         insertDictValue = new ORDictionary((*(ORDictionary*)dictIter->second)); 
00019         break;
00020       case kString: 
00021         insertDictValue = new ORDictValueS((*(ORDictValueS*)dictIter->second)); 
00022         break;
00023       case kReal: 
00024         insertDictValue = new ORDictValueR((*(ORDictValueR*)dictIter->second)); 
00025         break;
00026       case kInt: 
00027         insertDictValue = new ORDictValueI((*(ORDictValueI*)dictIter->second)); 
00028         break;
00029       case kBool: 
00030         insertDictValue = new ORDictValueB((*(ORDictValueB*)dictIter->second)); 
00031         break;
00032       case kArray: 
00033         insertDictValue = new ORDictValueA((*(ORDictValueA*)dictIter->second)); 
00034         break;
00035     }
00036     if (insertDictValue) {
00037       LoadEntry(dictIter->first, insertDictValue);
00038     } else {
00039       ORLog(kError) << "DictValue type not found!" << std::endl;
00040     }
00041   }

00052 ORVDictValue* ORDictionary::LookUp(std::string key, char delimiter) 
00053 {
00054   std::map<const std::string, ORVDictValue*>::const_iterator dictIter;
00055   size_t delimPos = key.find(delimiter); 
00056   if (delimPos == std::string::npos) {
00057     dictIter = fDictMap.find(key); 
00058     if (dictIter==fDictMap.end()) {
00059       ORLog(kDebug) << "ORDictionary::LookUp(): could not find key " << key
00060                       << " in dictionary " << fName << std::endl;
00061       return NULL;
00062     }
00063     return dictIter->second; 
00064   } else {
00065     std::string nextDictName = key.substr(0, delimPos);
00066     std::string nextKeyName = key.substr(delimPos+1);
00067     const ORVDictValue* nextDict = LookUp(nextDictName);
00068     if (nextDict == NULL) return NULL;
00069     if (nextDict->GetValueType() != kDict) {
00070       ORLog(kDebug) << "ORDictionary::LookUp(): key " << nextDictName 
00071                     << " in dictionary " << fName << " is not a dictionary (ValueType = " 
00072                     << nextDict->GetValueType() << ")." << std::endl;
00073       return NULL;
00074     }
00075     return ((ORDictionary*) nextDict)->LookUp(nextKeyName);
00076   }
00077 }
